    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-04T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-04T15:00:00-05:00" n="547"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d547">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4576: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1"
                            type="from">Wilson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-04T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 4, 1932—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 4—5 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>53. With reference to resolution of the Assembly adopted this afternoon
                    transmitted by <persName corresp="#p_GPB1">Gilbert</persName>, I have received
                    following letter from <persName corresp="#p_DSE1">Drummond</persName> dated
                    today: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The Assembly this afternoon adopted the accompanying resolution
                            regarding the cessation of hostilities in the vicinity of Shanghai
                            which, as you will see, invites the cooperation of the powers having
                            special interests in the Shanghai Settlements.</p>
                        <p>The British, French and Italian representatives accepted this suggestion
                            for cooperation insofar as their respective Governments are concerned. I
                            should be very grateful if you could inform me if the American
                            Government would also be able to cooperate”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>In this connection see my 52, March 4, 6 p.m.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SSJ1">Simon</persName> informed me during course of debate
                    that the words in the first paragraph “and without prejudice to the other
                    measures therein envisaged” had been inserted at his instance because he thought
                    this would be more satisfactory to you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WHR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
